#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/language/builtin/index.rst:78
msgid ""
"This is a frontend convenience wrapper that keeps a `BufferLoad` argument in "
"the resulting call so downstream passes can recover the referenced `tir."
"Buffer` (including strides/storage scope) *and* the `rw_mask` (read/write "
"intent) required by synchronization and safety checks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/language/builtin/index.rst:83
msgid ""
"The returned `tl.access_ptr` is expected to be lowered to `tir.builtin."
"tvm_access_ptr` later in the TileLang compilation pipeline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/language/builtin/index.rst:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/language/builtin/index.rst:86
msgid ""
"The base location to take the address of. Supported: - `tir.BufferLoad` (e."
"g. `A[i, j]`): pointer to that element - `tir.BufferRegion`: pointer to the "
"region minima - `tir.Buffer`: pointer to the beginning of the buffer - `tir."
"Var` with let-binding to one of the above (inside TileLang frame)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/language/builtin/index.rst:92
msgid ""
"Access mask for the pointer. Common string forms: `\"r\"`, `\"w\"`, "
"`\"rw\"`. Integer bitmask is also accepted (1=read, 2=write, 3=read-write)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/language/builtin/index.rst:95
msgid ""
"Optional per-axis extents. When provided and `extent` is not specified, the "
"1D `extent` passed to `tvm_access_ptr` is computed as the product of the "
"provided extents (padding leading dimensions with 1 if needed).  For "
"example: - `T.access_ptr(A[i], \"r\")` -> extent defaults to 1 (element "
"pointer) - `T.access_ptr(A[i], \"r\", 16)` -> extent=16 - `T.access_ptr(A[i, "
"j], \"r\", m, n)` -> extent=m*n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/language/builtin/index.rst:95
msgid ""
"Optional per-axis extents. When provided and `extent` is not specified, the "
"1D `extent` passed to `tvm_access_ptr` is computed as the product of the "
"provided extents (padding leading dimensions with 1 if needed)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/language/builtin/index.rst:99
msgid ""
"For example: - `T.access_ptr(A[i], \"r\")` -> extent defaults to 1 (element "
"pointer) - `T.access_ptr(A[i], \"r\", 16)` -> extent=16 - `T.access_ptr(A[i, "
"j], \"r\", m, n)` -> extent=m*n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/language/builtin/index.rst:104
msgid "Additional element offset from the base location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/language/builtin/index.rst:106
msgid ""
"Optional explicit 1D extent override (in elements). If provided, it takes "
"precedence over `*extents`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../autoapi/tilelang/language/builtin/index.rst:109
msgid ""
"If non-zero, the base linear offset is computed only over the leading "
"dimensions, ignoring the last `ignore_last_ndim` axes. This is useful when "
"treating an N-D buffer as a view of its trailing sub-tensor."
msgstr ""

